		<div class="post-558 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-automation category-core-applications category-technology category-testing category-ztpf-migration tag-technology-2 tag-travel-it-talent tag-travel-technology" >
        	
			<div class="col8"> 
            
                <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.igt.in/blog/it-helpdesk-moving-beyond-traditional-to-strategic-support-pillar-for-it-services/" title="Permalink to IT Helpdesk: Moving into strategic support for IT Services" rel="bookmark" >IT Helpdesk: Moving into strategic support for IT Services</a></h2>
    
                <ul class="post-by">
                                        <li>September 21, 2016</li>
                    <li class="last"><a href="http://www.igt.in/blog/it-helpdesk-moving-beyond-traditional-to-strategic-support-pillar-for-it-services/#respond" title="Comment on IT Helpdesk: Moving into strategic support for IT Services">No Comments</a></li>
                </ul>
            
				<p>With the rapid alignment of IT as a strategic investment and the digitization of work places has brought about bigger challenges and opportunities.   As organizations get more global, and dependencies on IT increases, the IT service desk has become more crucial as a specialized single point of contact for all IT requirements. But driving business transformation or transition can be a double-edged sword.  Looking inwards at the Travel industry with its multiple partners and stakeholders, the risk of tripping over technology can cause massive&hellip; <a class="readmore" href="http://www.igt.in/blog/it-helpdesk-moving-beyond-traditional-to-strategic-support-pillar-for-it-services/">Continue Reading &rarr;</a></p>
