                    <li class="last"><a href="http://www.igt.in/blog/is-automation-the-end-of-mishandled-airline-baggage/#respond" title="Comment on Is Automation the end of Mishandled Airline Baggage">No Comments</a></li>
                </ul>
            
				<p>Passengers expect their bags to take off and land with them, driving one the biggest pain points for Aviation industry whenever baggage handling goes south. Let’s put this into numbers &#8211; the operational cost of baggagehandling is approx. ten dollars for an airline. However, when it’s mishandled, the same cost goes upto$100. And this is not taking into account the loss of a customer satisfaction or the impact of negative social media reviews.With 2016 marking the digitization of baggage handling systems, industry initiatives and IATA&hellip; <a class="readmore" href="http://www.igt.in/blog/is-automation-the-end-of-mishandled-airline-baggage/">Continue Reading &rarr;</a></p>
