		<div class="post-488 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-airline-disruption-management category-automation category-business-intelligence-and-data-warehousing category-hospitality category-mobility category-technology tag-baggage-handling-mobility-apps tag-hospitality-apps tag-interglobe-technologies-mobility-solutions tag-iot-travel tag-mobility tag-mobility-in-travel tag-travel-and-hospitality tag-travel-apps" >
        	
			<div class="col8"> 
            
                <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.igt.in/blog/potential-of-an-iot-in-the-future-of-travel/" title="Permalink to Potential of an IoT in the future of Travel" rel="bookmark" >Potential of an IoT in the future of Travel</a></h2>
    
                <ul class="post-by">
                                        <li>May 24, 2016</li>
                    <li class="last"><a href="http://www.igt.in/blog/potential-of-an-iot-in-the-future-of-travel/#respond" title="Comment on Potential of an IoT in the future of Travel">No Comments</a></li>
                </ul>
            
				<p>The blurring of lines between the physical and virtual worlds, especially with the IoT, (Internet of Things) has created a seamless connection between organizations and their audiences. The remarkable speed at which it’s infiltrated each and every aspect of Travel industry from beacons to keyless entry, social to security and communications to collective intelligence has brought new-age challenges and opportunities. Today, one billion people in the world are using four billion connected things (IoT 2016). What’s the potential of an IoT solution in the Internet-of-Everything&hellip; <a class="readmore" href="http://www.igt.in/blog/potential-of-an-iot-in-the-future-of-travel/">Continue Reading &rarr;</a></p>
